    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I've started using Cython much more extensively than I previously have, and am looking to add more comprehensive C++ wrappers for code.\r\n\r\nA simple example would be the `<algorithms>` [header](https://github.com/cython/cython/blob/master/Cython/Includes/libcpp/algorithm.pxd), which currently has a very limited subset of the C++ algorithms declarations. I would like to submit PRs to wrap a lot of this functionality more comprehensively (to avoid duplicating this code myself), and was wondering if these PRs would be welcome by Cython?",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
