            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Well, the best way to prove that the declarations are correct and work in Cython is to back them up by a little test example. \r\nYou can see how that is done in `tests/run/cpp_stl*.pyx`, especially `cpp_stl_cpp11.pyx`. Add a test function there, add a (Python) doctest, then run it with `python[3] runtests.py -vv --backend=cpp --debug cpp_stl_cpp11` to see if it passes.",
